history.content: **UPDATE 4/18:  To be able to implement this, we will have to create a faux discussion and/or lab section that will be offered at no particular time and in no particular room that all students who enroll in CS 1xx will select.  The actual sections at specific times in specific locations will still exist at classes.berkeley.edu but not in calcentral.  The faux section will create no conflicts and it will have at least as many seats as the lecture so the waitlist can still be processed in lecture waitlist order.  It should be possible to enroll in any non-cross-listed CS course starting between 9am and noon on Wednesday 4/19.

So far it seems a huge swath of EECS classes are suffering this issue, with regards to Fall 2017: 

Data c8, CS 70, 160, 162, 164, 168, 170, 186, and 189 all have confirmed issues with the shopping cart and enrollment due to a mess-up with the new discussion section policy. 

The shopping cart issue can be circumvented by importing a schedule from schedule planner, but no workaround is as yet known for enrollment. 

CS161 seems to have discussion sections, so shopping cart works fine, but has enrollment issues due to "department permission" needed.  (Resolved according to @3831)

CS188 and 169 are known issues. 188 is still looking for a professor and 169 has a special enrollment setup this semester.
